post_text:
Now hiring Special Education ParaProfessionals

Salary: $15.44 - $17.84 per hour depending on qualifications
Schedule: hours are on student days and vary by assignment

Required Qualifications:
A high school diploma or GED and one of the following: An AA, AS or AAS (or higher) degree, or Passing score of 460 (or higher) on the ParaPro Assessment

(For more information on the ParaPro assessment, contact Educational Testing Services at (800) 772-9476 or www.ets.org/parpro)
Pass training for full certification of Professional Crisis Management (PCM)

In addition:
* Ability to lift up to 50 lbs. and restrain students in emergency situations
* Strong communication and interpersonal skills
* Ability to maintain confidentiality
* Completion of any required training necessary for the position

If you have additional questions about the ParaPro Assessment, please contact Kris Jurgensen at kmjurgensen@rwps.org.

Apply here: https://redwing.k12.mn.us/page/8424

Parents! Check your email! You should have an email from Superintendent Anderson outlining what we know so far. We know you are trying to manage child care, really hard decisions, and overwhelming stress at this time. Most of our staff and teachers are faced with some of the same decisions you are, so please know we are doing our best to plan and give options.

But we feel a little like we are building on sand. We ask for your continued flexibility and patience as we move closer to the first day of school.

If you are looking for the document, you can find the most updated English and Spanish versions here: https://redwing.k12.mn.us/page/hot_news/view/1479

post_text:
Community! It's the WINGER WAY.

Technology has been an integral tool in delivering education during this time. And our community partners continue to provide desperately needed resources.

Recently, the Wings - Red Wing and three community philanthropists pledged $50,000 to pay for seven smart boards and seven large-screen televisions for classrooms at Jefferson School. This technology will enable teachers to provide consistent and continuous instruction for students at Jefferson School while students are socially distancing.

We are truly grateful for their support. Please join us in thanking them for their support of our students!

Material Return Information:

**Students in Grades 1-5 in 2020-21
Unless your child is receiving Extended School Year (ESY) Services this summer, we need parents of children in grades 1 – 5 in the 2020-21 school year to return Chromebooks, charging cords, Chromebook cases, textbooks, and library books during times listed below.

**Students in Grades 6-12 in 2020-21

Parents of students in grades 6-12 in the 2020-21 school year should return Chromebooks only if they need repair, textbooks, and library books during times listed below.

Drop-Off Dates and Times

You may drop them off curbside by the RWHS Courtyard Café (door 40) on:

Thursday, July 16th from 12 - 6 pm
Tuesday, July 21st from 7 am – 1 pm
Students in Extended School Year (ESY) Services this Summer

Students receiving ESY will return their computer equipment later this summer.

shared_text:
Red Wing Water Park
May 12 at 1:43 PM ·

Last night, the Red Wing City Council voted to close the Red Wing Waterpark for the summer of 2020. The Council cited the inability to assure the proper safety of guests and staff as well as not being able to properly train staff with social distancing in place.

We know how much the community values the Red Wing Waterpark, so it’s being closed only after exhausting every effort. But we assure you, we are going to come back stronger than ever in 2021!

Those who already purchased season passes will be contacted in the next week or two in regards to a refund or possibly having the season pass get pushed into next summer.

post_text:
Food Service Updates:
Meal delivery will continue into the month of May. As we approach the summer months, more information will be coming in May as Food Service works to solidify summer plans.

RWPS Food Service Department will be closed on Monday, May 25th. However, meals will be packaged for the extended weekend, and included with the meal distribution on Friday, May 22nd. Meal Delivery will pick up again on Wednesday, May 27th as normal.

Reminder that meals are for children 18 and younger – One meal per child per day. Pick-up at the High School is from 11-11:45 a.m. and Sunnyside Elem. is 11 – 12:00 p.m. No meals will be served after those times, per state requirements.

Families may want to consider bringing a bag, backpack or cooler to assist in getting meals back to their homes and stored accordingly, as we get into the warmer months.

* Individuals picking up should be free of fever or illness.
* Wash hands or use sanitizer prior to picking up meals.

post_text:
PBIS - Positive Behavioral Interventions and Supports
Creating a positive climate for learning

As of Fall of 2019, all Red Wing K-12 schools are PBIS schools and are currently in or have completed the two-year Minnesota Department of Education PBIS Cohort Training.

What success have we seen?
We have shared language and expectations at the building levels, which focuses on proactive strategies, school-wide rewards, and assemblies to teach expectations. We have also seen a shift in our adult behavior when working with struggling students as well as providing positive interactions on a daily, hourly, minute-by-minute basis.

The PBIS team looks forward to sharing more information as we strive to create a culture that improves social, emotional, behavioral and academic outcomes for all students.

The PBIS team looks forward to sharing more information as we strive to create a culture that improves social, emotional, behavioral and academic outcomes for all students.

post_text:
"Went to all four schools in about an hour. Front seat is full of 4 kids' school supplies. So, surreal. And amazing to think the staff went through each kid's desk, and locker/cubby and had to put their things in a black bag. How depressing that must have been. To not say goodbye to the kids, no last hug, no pictures to remember them by. To not even see the kids in the car. I just want to say thank you, to all the staff at each school. I appreciate all of you" -- Ashley

"5 kids, 3 different schools, all under an hour. So organized! THANK YOU to all the staff for all the hard work you have put in and continue to do in making this a success." --Kelly

School supply pickup is today and tomorrow (Friday, March 27) We are working hard to ensure a smooth transition to distance learning and appreciate the efforts of teachers, administrators, parents and students of our community!

shared_text:
Red Wing High School is in Red Wing, Minnesota.
March 22 at 1:14 PM · Red Wing, MN ·

Can we start something fun here in Red Wing and work together on another community project?

Many you have probably read the children’s book or heard the song “Going on a Bear Hunt.” Let’s work together to put Wingers around town (in your window/lawn/car window/etc.).

1. These are visual signs of encouragement for our RWPS students in a difficult time.
2. Red Wing families can go for a drive or a walk and do a “Winger Hunt!” What a great way to get a break from the house while still being safe.

You can hang shirts, jerseys, a printed logo, chalk your sidewalk, paint your window... be creative. Then report back and let us know how many Wingers you saw! #wingerpride @ Red Wing, Minnesota

Here is the updated meal flier in both English and Spanish. Food Service has added 3 additional sites and now has included weekend meal coverage (which was included on Friday meal deliveries).

1. Special thanks to Community Ed for all the resources and help during this time assisting Food Service and our Emergency Personnel providing daycare coverage!

2. The Food Service Department is not taking volunteers at this time, but Goodhue County Health and Human Services is looking. If interested, please email Lisa at lisa.woodford@co.goodhue.mn.us or by phone (651) 385-6128.

3. Please remember to donate when able to area food shelves, as they will need resources in the weeks to come. Non-Perishables only.

4. Reminder that numbers are changing daily and so projecting meal counts can be challenging for sites across the district. Be patient as we navigate these challenges to reach the children in the community.

Free Internet Access for Selected Families

A local cable provider is offering two months of free broadband service to eligible low-income households who are new customers.

Red Wing High School Choirs
March 13 at 9:55 AM ·

We are sorry to say that we have been advised to cancel our upcoming 9th-12th grade choral concert on Monday, 3/16, due to the COVID-19 outbreak. It is certainly less than ideal, but we are acting in the best interest of our students and audience members. In lieu of the performance, we will be live-streaming each of the choirs during their class time through the RWHS Choir's Facebook page. The students have worked very hard on their music, and this will provide a way for them to share it with you.

The schedule for the live stream is listed below:

9th Grade Choir: Friday, 3/13 - approximately 2:15 p.m.

Bella Voce: Monday, 3/16 - approximately 12:00 p.m.

Concert Choir: Tuesday, 3/17 - approximately 10:30 a.m.

**If you are unable to watch the videos live, you can still watch the videos afterwards on the Facebook page**

post_text:
WINGER FLIGHT PATHS

These are our students who received Precision Exams Certificates from their courses this last semester. These tests indicate industry-recognized standards and skills to show competency in a variety of career field areas. In the first semester, Red Wing High School had 67 certificate earners showing growth from the 73 certificate earners last year. Tests included Greenhouse Management, Automotive Service Fundamentals, Welding Technician I, Animal Science II, Veterinary Assistant, Veterinary Technician, and Economics. This is one way that students are able to bolster their resumes and applications giving them a competitive advantage moving into their futures.

post_text:
Ms. Seefeldt tells students, "Our job at school is to give everyone what they need to be successful and that can look different than someone else and that's okay, it's what makes us individuals and unique. The world would be boring if we were all the same"

Our new Reset & Reflect Room is now open at Burnside School. It is available for general education students who find themselves needing a moment to reset and reflect. The emotional health of all our students is important to us, and this new space, along with the direction of Ms. Seefeldt is just one of the ways we are adapting to serve the needs of our students.

Have questions or comments? Feel free to contact: Emily Seefeldt at easeefeldt@rwps.org or Kim Cory at kacory@rwps.org
